Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.99,0:01:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Jules Verne once wrote,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.92,0:01:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"Put two ships in the open sea
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.42,0:01:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"without wind or tide,\Nthey will come together."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.85,0:01:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's how my parents met. Like\Ntwo ships destined for each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.19,0:01:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- We are something else.\N- Try Arthur Treacher...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.40,0:01:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.31,0:02:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Easy. You weren't breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.09,0:02:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They were from different worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.96,0:02:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But life, like the sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.07,0:02:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}has a way of bringing\Npeople together.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.61,0:03:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.18,0:03:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I was gonna make you some eggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.29,0:03:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Just don't eat my dog, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.29,0:03:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.62,0:03:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I made tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.13,0:03:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Go on, try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.63,0:03:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll make you better.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.82,0:03:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, uh, who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.19,0:04:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Atlanna.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.50,0:04:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Queen of Atlantis.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.97,0:04:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.87,0:04:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Tom. Keeper of lighthouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.97,0:04:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She had fled an\Narranged marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.04,0:04:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Left her whole world behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.08,0:04:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But in my father's lighthouse,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.28,0:04:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}she found something unexpected.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.38,0:05:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And my father found\Nthe love of his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.99,0:05:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Category 4 Hurricane Arthur
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.56,0:05:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}is due to make landfall\Nsometime after 2:00 p.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.46,0:05:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How about Arthur?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.40,0:05:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,After the hurricane?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.87,0:05:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,After a legend.\NHe's a king, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.57,0:05:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He's more than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.38,0:05:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He's living proof our\Npeople can coexist.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.05,0:05:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He could unite\Nour worlds one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.96,0:05:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And the trident could only be\Nwielded by the strongest Atlantean.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.09,0:05:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And it gave King Atlan\Nmastery over the seven seas.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.43,0:05:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It made him so powerful that\Nthe ocean itself became jealous
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.64,0:05:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and sent a terrible\Nearthquake to destroy Atlantis.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.11,0:05:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Down it fell, to the\Nbottom of the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.51,0:06:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But, legend has it that one\Nday a new king will come
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.11,0:06:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,who will use the\Npower of the trident
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.45,0:06:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to put Atlantis\Nback together again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.83,0:06:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Take him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.05,0:06:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Queen Atlanna,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.41,0:06:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}by the authority of King Orvax,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.55,0:06:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}you are ordered\Nto return to Atlantis.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.65,0:06:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Atlanna!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.52,0:06:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But Atlantis' memory is long...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.83,0:06:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And its king\Nrefused to let her go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.21,0:07:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,- Atlanna!\N- Tom!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.48,0:07:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- My weapon!\N- Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.84,0:07:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Their two worlds were\Nnever meant to meet,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.78,0:07:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and I was a product of a\Nlove that never should've been.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.18,0:07:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to do\Nthis, Atlanna. Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.15,0:07:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No. They will always find me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.29,0:07:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time, they'll send an army.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.12,0:07:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to go back. It is\Nthe only way to save him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.83,0:08:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Save you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.14,0:08:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Where I come from...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.81,0:08:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The sea carries our tears away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.35,0:08:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.68,0:08:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you feel them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.22,0:08:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I will return to\Nyou. When it's safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.43,0:08:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,One day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.56,0:08:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Right here, at sunrise.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.44,0:08:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be together again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.87,0:08:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You stay strong,\Nmy little prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.74,0:08:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll always be with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.22,0:08:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let him forget me. Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.25,0:09:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,All life came from the sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.85,0:09:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,so if we want to\Nunderstand ourselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.12,0:09:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,we must journey\Nto where we began.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.09,0:09:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, today, we have better maps of\NMars than we do of our own sea floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.96,0:09:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, closer. Come on, fishy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.09,0:09:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,- Come on. Come over here.\N- Boys!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.56,0:09:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop that. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.83,0:09:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Come along.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.00,0:09:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye, fishy. Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.94,0:09:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My name's Arthur. What's yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.07,0:09:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,- You guys hungry? Me, too.\N- Check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.28,0:09:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Arthur is talking to the fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.81,0:09:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Such a freak, Arthur.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.52,0:10:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,- Stop!\N- What are you gonna do about it, freak?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.15,0:10:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it! Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.32,0:10:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.63,0:11:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an5\c&H51ab2b&}Improved by{\c&Hf8fc03&} {\b1}KID{\b0} {\c}\N\N{\an5\c&H51ab2b&}Resynced by{\c&Hf8fc03&} {\b1}KID{\b0} {\c}\N\N{\an5\c&H51ab2b&}Enjoy the movie(s) / show(s)
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.04,0:12:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.31,0:12:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, let's go. Move it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.01,0:12:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on. Hurry up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.29,0:12:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, we've secured the captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.99,0:12:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Distress signal's disabled.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.86,0:12:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We're running dark again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.49,0:12:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But they heard it.\NYou can count on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.89,0:12:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll make you a deal. I won't\Ntell you how to captain...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.53,0:12:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't tell\Nme how to pirate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.81,0:12:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the rest of the crew?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.48,0:12:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Decided discretion was\Nthe better part of valor
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.31,0:12:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and sealed themselves\Nup in the torpedo bay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.42,0:12:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Our reputation precedes us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.12,0:12:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Your reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.79,0:12:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This is your win.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.03,0:12:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.93,0:13:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't take that piece of junk.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.20,0:13:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the love of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.13,0:13:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I never told you\Nthe story behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.40,0:13:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This was your grandfather's.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.91,0:13:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He was one of the Navy's first\Nfrogmen during World War II.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.68,0:13:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He was so stealthy in the water,\Nhis unit nicknamed him Manta.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.42,0:13:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But after the war, his\Ncountry forgot about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.19,0:13:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So, he went back to the sea,\Nscavenging and surviving with his wit...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.29,0:13:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And this knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.33,0:13:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave it to me\Nwhen I was your age.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.16,0:13:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And now it's yours, son.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.70,0:14:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Did we just hit something?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.13,0:14:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Something hit us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.30,0:14:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, there's\Nsomething out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.80,0:14:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Another submarine?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.00,0:14:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... No. I think it's a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.05,0:15:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.19,0:15:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Alpha, to the right. Bravo\Nteam, sweep the passageway.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.22,0:15:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Permission to come aboard?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.14,0:17:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Aquaman!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.84,0:17:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I've waited a\Nlong time for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.52,0:17:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I supposed to\Nknow who you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.36,0:18:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I scavenge the high seas.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.49,0:18:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the Aquaman.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.76,0:18:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We were bound to\Nmeet at some point.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.04,0:18:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's not make it a habit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.00,0:18:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.36,0:19:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Ow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.91,0:19:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.24,0:19:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad? Ow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.51,0:19:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's your kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.95,0:19:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Shame on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.06,0:19:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Boys got yourselves\Ninto this mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.83,0:19:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Get yourselves out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.09,0:19:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.54,0:19:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.25,0:20:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.32,0:20:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.69,0:20:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Help me! He's trapped!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.52,0:20:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't leave him like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.12,0:20:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.53,0:20:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You killed innocent people.\NYou ask the sea for mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.21,0:20:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Get outta here! I got this!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.51,0:20:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up, I'm not leaving you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.18,0:20:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to live, so you\Ncan kill that son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.42,0:20:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- Now, go!\N- No!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.76,0:20:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,- Go!\N- Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.16,0:20:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.83,0:20:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.62,0:21:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.85,0:21:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.26,0:22:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I always know where to find you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.70,0:22:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Old habits.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.94,0:22:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,- Come on, I'll buy you breakfast.\N- All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.78,0:22:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You want me to have them\Nput that in a sippy cup for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.12,0:22:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it that I can\Nbreathe underwater,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.89,0:23:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,but you can still drink\Nme under the table?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.29,0:23:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my superpower.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.13,0:23:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A Russian submarine
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.73,0:23:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}hijacked late last night\Nby high-tech pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.97,0:23:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The same pirates\Nwho are suspected
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.10,0:23:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}in connection with the disappearance\Nof the Navy's highly classified
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.97,0:23:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}prototype stealth submarine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.47,0:23:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And a further development, we\Nnow have unconfirmed reports
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.81,0:23:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}that the metahuman dubbed by\Nsocial media as "The Aquaman"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.55,0:23:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}was responsible for\Nthis daring rescue.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.52,0:23:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.85,0:23:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Bullshit. You're doing\Nit, aren't you? Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.02,0:23:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What Vulko trained you to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.29,0:23:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew you couldn't stand\Non the sidelines forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.53,0:23:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mother always\Nknew you were special.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.63,0:23:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't even start.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.20,0:23:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,She believed you'd be the\None to unite our two worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.27,0:23:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Just stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.64,0:23:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever Atlantis' problems\Nare, you're bigger than them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.61,0:23:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Atlantis murdered my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.65,0:23:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know that for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.15,0:23:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.51,0:24:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They killed her. For\Nloving you and having me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.92,0:24:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And you know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.76,0:24:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Son, one day you're gonna\Nhave to stop blaming yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.97,0:24:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, buddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.64,0:24:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You that fish boy from the TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.28,0:24:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, great.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.68,0:24:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's "fish man."\NWhat do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.08,0:24:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you what I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.76,0:24:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Could we get a picture with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.46,0:24:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You're like our local hero, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.40,0:24:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It would mean a\Nlot. Just a quick...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.60,0:24:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.94,0:24:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- All right. Let's do this.\N- Don't touch me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.54,0:24:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, that's exactly right.\NI'm gonna go down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.84,0:25:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There we go. Everybody smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.80,0:25:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He understands the\Nsignificance of this meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.84,0:26:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll hear you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.95,0:26:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- King Orm.\N- King Nereus.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.16,0:26:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You picked a meeting place too\Nclose to the surface for my liking.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.59,0:26:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't recognize\Nthe Council of the Kings?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.43,0:26:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,In Atlan's time, when the\NSeven Kingdoms were one,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.83,0:26:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,our ancestors gathered here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.54,0:26:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Atlantis sat here at\Nthe head of the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.04,0:26:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Xebel, as always, by his side.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.94,0:26:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Brine. Fishermen.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.81,0:26:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The Deserters and the\NTrench had not yet fallen.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.05,0:26:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The Lost Nation\Nhad not yet vanished.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.15,0:26:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Together, they were the greatest\Nempire the world had ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.12,0:26:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, I sit\Non Atlan's throne,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.12,0:26:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,shackled by archaic\Nlaws and politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.82,0:26:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,While the threat above\Nus grows undeniably...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.99,0:27:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Violence has always\Nplagued the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.10,0:27:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They will destroy themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.53,0:27:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Not before destroying us first.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.37,0:27:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We have been hiding long enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.64,0:27:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The time has come\Nfor Atlantis to rise again.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.44,0:27:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We honor you, King Nereus,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.01,0:27:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,by inviting Xebel to\Nbe the first kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.41,0:27:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to join King Orm's alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.72,0:27:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,As if you had a choice, Vulko.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.55,0:27:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,By law, you need four\Nof the Seven Kingdoms
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.72,0:27:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to ascend and attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.39,0:27:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The Lost Nation and the\NDeserters have long perished.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.59,0:27:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The Trench are\Nnothing but animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.66,0:27:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The Brine will never join you,\Nand the Fishermen are cowards.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.30,0:27:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Without me and my army to\Nconvince them, your plans are stillborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.43,0:27:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But I know what you really want.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.80,0:27:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you've obtained the\Npledge of the four kingdoms,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.67,0:27:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you will be ordained
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.48,0:27:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Ocean Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.21,0:27:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That is merely a title.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.21,0:27:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm no fool, King Orm.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.22,0:27:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,As Ocean Master,\Nyou'll be commander
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.68,0:27:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of the greatest military\Nmight on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.49,0:28:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the natural\Nchoice to lead it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.62,0:28:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.73,0:28:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the rumors\Nthat there's another?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.36,0:28:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,An Atlantean, living\Namong the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.97,0:28:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,One of royal blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.43,0:28:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You may sit on the throne of\NAtlantis, but your claim to it is weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.34,0:28:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you possibly\Nhope to unite the empire?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.47,0:28:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother's bastard has\Nnever even been to Atlantis.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.81,0:28:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,His loyalty is to the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.82,0:28:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Surface-dwellers! To arms!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.04,0:28:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Your king is injured!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.94,0:30:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not trying to start a war.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.88,0:30:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The war has already begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.61,0:30:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it's time we send\Nthem a message they'll hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.55,0:30:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm good.\N- Stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.92,0:30:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,- Here're the keys.\N- Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.72,0:30:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go home and work\Non your ta moko. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.12,0:30:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If your grandpops\Nwas still alive,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.63,0:30:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,he'd be banging our\Nheads for not finishing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.66,0:30:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he would, but there\Nis plenty of time for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.47,0:30:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We gotta get you to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.57,0:30:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.38,0:30:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been looking for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.95,0:30:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, no, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.28,0:30:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I need you to come\Nwith me to Atlantis.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.65,0:30:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, I'm gonna\Ntell you the same thing
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.48,0:30:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that I told that\Nrusty starfish Vulko.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.49,0:30:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Except nicer,\Nbecause you're a lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.52,0:30:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,No, thank you.\NI'm not interested.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.52,0:30:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You defeated Steppenwolf\Nand saved Atlantis.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.69,0:30:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That had nothing\Nto do with Atlantis.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.86,0:30:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Your half-brother King Orm is about\Nto declare war upon the surface world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.20,0:31:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Billions will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.14,0:31:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Your people and mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.37,0:31:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We must stop him.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.81,0:31:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And how do you\Npropose we do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.71,0:31:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You are the firstborn\Nson of Queen Atlanna.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.18,0:31:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The throne is\Nyours by birthright.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.48,0:31:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The only way to stop this\Nwar and save both worlds
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.99,0:31:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is for you to take your\Nrightful place as king.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.26,0:31:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You think if I just show up,\NOrm's gonna give up the throne?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.40,0:31:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the bastard son of the\Nqueen your people executed.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.97,0:31:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust me. I am no king.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.60,0:31:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.47,0:31:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's awesome. Cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.87,0:31:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But, Vulko seems to believe\Nin you for some reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.84,0:31:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's why I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.48,0:31:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Vulko has learned of the\Nlocation of the Lost Trident of Atlan.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.38,0:31:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh, fairy tales. It's a myth.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.45,0:31:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a myth.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.99,0:31:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,With the Sacred Trident,\Nthe people will listen to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.09,0:31:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You can then claim your\Nbirthright and dethrone Orm.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.39,0:32:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,My birthright? It\Ndied with my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.26,0:32:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But I promise you\Nthis. If Orm attacks,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.66,0:32:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I will treat him exactly the same\Nway your people treated her.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.17,0:32:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,With no mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.06,0:33:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That submarine was barely\Noperational, but it served its purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.67,0:33:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,One of your kind intervened.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.43,0:33:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He is not one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.50,0:33:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He killed my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.18,0:33:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Our transaction has ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.31,0:33:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep the money. I want Aquaman.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.72,0:34:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.19,0:34:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.86,0:35:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.43,0:35:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Pops!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.20,0:35:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Pops!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.40,0:35:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Pops.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.54,0:35:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on! He's not breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.27,0:35:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Move! Let me help.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.12,0:35:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Pops.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.03,0:35:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.51,0:36:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't even know your name.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.81,0:36:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Princess Y'Mera\NXebella Challa.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.28,0:36:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You may call me Mera.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.35,0:36:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Mera.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.04,0:36:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear God.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.21,0:36:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This was Orm's doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.65,0:36:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The worst is yet to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.16,0:37:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There's a flash\Nflood warning here
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.99,0:37:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}that was just extended\Nfor a couple hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.70,0:37:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Unprecedented sights\Nfrom all over the world today.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.30,0:37:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We are seeing warships and\Ntrash washed up by massive waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.97,0:37:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}These extraordinary scenes\Nof coastlines deluged with waste
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.31,0:37:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and garbage are taking\Nplace all over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.81,0:37:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Decades of pollution has\Nbeen thrown back onto land.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.08,0:37:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Many are asking the question,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.91,0:37:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"Was this a natural\Ndisaster or something else?"
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.28,0:37:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No. This was no\Nnatural disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.88,0:37:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They threw out our\Ngarbage and our warships.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.22,0:37:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This was our first contact\Nwith the people of Atlantis.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.62,0:37:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There you go again with\Nyour insane Atlantean theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.93,0:37:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You have absolutely\Nno proof, Dr. Shin.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.83,0:37:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Open your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.26,0:37:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We already have an\NAtlantean living among us,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.83,0:37:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and his name is Aquaman.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.14,0:37:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.87,0:37:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the exact spot that Vulko\Ngave me my first swimming lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.08,0:37:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to forget all the\Nteaching of the surface world
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.42,0:38:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and go deeper to uncover\Nyour Atlantean instincts.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.19,0:38:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But I already know how to swim.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.46,0:38:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Not even close.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.46,0:38:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Just so we're clear,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.70,0:38:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll help you stop this war.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.33,0:38:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, I'm done.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.83,0:38:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe that's for the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.09,0:38:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The ocean is more than\Nour life source, Arthur.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.39,0:38:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It is who we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.79,0:38:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, you can talk underwater?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.89,0:38:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I can talk underwater, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.40,0:38:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This is awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.67,0:38:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we can do\Nmore than just talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.64,0:39:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Being Atlantean means more\Nthan just being able to breathe water.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.78,0:39:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Your body is equipped to survive\Nthe extreme cold and pressure,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.79,0:39:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and your eyes adjust\Nto see in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.28,0:39:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This is awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.31,0:40:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Vulko, when can\NI meet my mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.01,0:40:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon, my young prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.35,0:40:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're ready, I'll take\Nyou to Atlantis to meet the queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.03,0:40:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I hid my ship in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.57,0:40:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, I'm not\Ngetting in that thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.40,0:40:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, to get where we're\Ngoing, you're gonna have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.34,0:40:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Your fish ship has been\Nmarinating in chum butter.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.51,0:40:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna come out\Nsmelling like swamp butt.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.51,0:40:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That'd be an improvement.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.15,0:40:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yup. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.58,0:41:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the point in having\Na bridge underwater?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.68,0:41:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The Gateway Bridge is a\Nremnant of the Old World.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.08,0:41:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also the only way\Nin or out of the Capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.09,0:41:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Why can't they just\Ngo over the walls?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.62,0:42:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Security is impenetrable.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.26,0:42:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if they did manage\Nto evade the guards,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.99,0:42:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,they'd never get past\Nthe hydro-cannons.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.06,0:42:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,People try to\Nsneak in all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.43,0:42:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.88,0:42:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.15,0:42:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Customs and border control.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.59,0:42:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. I have\Ndiplomatic clearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.47,0:42:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome home.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.12,0:43:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a safe house\Ndown in the Old City.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.38,0:43:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The Highborns never\Nventure to the sea floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.65,0:43:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.92,0:44:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.59,0:44:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We use this air pocket as\Nan extra layer of precaution.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.92,0:44:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Only the Highborns can\Nbreathe water as well as air.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.49,0:44:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus, it keeps the animals out.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.13,0:44:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They get kind of messy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.80,0:44:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Vulko. Here I am, old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.70,0:44:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,After all these years, you\Nfinally get what you wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.37,0:44:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Arthur, I wish it was\Nunder better circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.21,0:44:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe Orm attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.54,0:44:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't an attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.48,0:44:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Legally, he's not\Nallowed to yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.82,0:44:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What he did to your surface\Nwarships was merely a warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.25,0:44:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What provoked it?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.79,0:44:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,King Orm and your father\Nwere ambushed by the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.42,0:44:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,By the surface?\NI don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.06,0:44:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,They still think\NAtlantis is a fairy tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.99,0:44:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.70,0:44:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A surface warship fired at us.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.57,0:45:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Xebel sides with Atlantis,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.30,0:45:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,giving Orm a fleet big enough to\Nforce the other two kingdoms to join him.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.21,0:45:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If we're going to prevent this\Nwar, you must dethrone him now.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.78,0:45:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,How many times do I have to\Ntell you? I don't wanna be king.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.05,0:45:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.82,0:45:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Once he is named Ocean\NMaster, it'll be too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.32,0:45:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The power at his disposal will be\Nunlike anything you have ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.05,0:45:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm from the surface. No one\Nis gonna take me seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.73,0:45:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay? I don't even\Nknow where to begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.29,0:45:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,By winning the hearts\Nand minds of the people
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.76,0:45:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,by proving to them that you're\Nworthy, and retrieving this.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.40,0:45:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.21,0:45:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I already got one of those.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.04,0:45:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Not like this one, you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.31,0:45:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Lost\NTrident of Atlan.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.98,0:45:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I know the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.22,0:45:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more than\Na story. It's real.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.72,0:45:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was forged by the greatest\Nweapon masters in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.76,0:46:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Crafted from Poseidon's\Nsteel for King Atlan,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.33,0:46:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the first ruler of Atlantis.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.53,0:46:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Legend says the trident was imbued\Nwith the power to command the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.14,0:46:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So what happened to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.97,0:46:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,To know that is to go back to\Nthe time before the Great Fall,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.58,0:46:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}when King Atlan\Nruled over all that was,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.81,0:46:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}when the kingdoms\Nof Atlantis were one.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.02,0:46:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was a time of great prosperity\Nand technological advancement.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.53,0:46:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We had unlocked the\Nsecret of unlimited energy
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.16,0:46:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}at a time when\Nthe rest of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.90,0:46:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}still thought the\Nearth was flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.10,0:46:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But we became too ambitious,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.30,0:46:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}too hungry for power.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.19,0:47:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The ocean swallowed\Nus, and Atlantis sank.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.26,0:47:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But the very power that\Ncollapsed our civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.20,0:47:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}also paved the\Nway to our future.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.50,0:47:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It gave us the ability\Nto breathe underwater.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.40,0:47:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And so, we evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.41,0:47:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Others regressed, became savage.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.38,0:47:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And the king lived out the remainder\Nof his days in self-imposed exile.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.72,0:47:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Neither he nor the trident\Nwere ever seen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.09,0:47:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,One of our archeological teams\Nuncovered this a few months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.36,0:47:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an ancient recording\Ndating back to the First Dynasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.23,0:47:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe it contains Atlan's\Nfinal message to his people
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.97,0:47:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and the whereabouts\Nof the Sacred Trident.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.04,0:47:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what does it say?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.47,0:47:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't know. The\Ntechnology's too old.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.24,0:47:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The cylinder bears the\Nmarkings of the Deserter Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.01,0:48:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You must take it there\Nand retrieve the message.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.81,0:48:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The clue to Atlan's final\Nresting place is inside of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.03,0:48:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Border Defense. You are\Nunder arrest for illegal entry.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.20,0:48:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.11,0:48:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You mustn't be seen here!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.83,0:49:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't suppose you want\Nto talk about this, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.97,0:49:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither do I.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.88,0:50:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In the name of His Highness,\NKing Orm, I place you under arrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.44,0:50:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to Atlantis...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.31,0:50:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.78,0:50:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe\Nyou're finally here.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.92,0:50:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard so many\Nstories about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.53,0:51:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All these years, I've been\Nashamed of my mother
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.73,0:51:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,for defiling herself\Nwith a surface-dweller.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.87,0:51:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Ashamed of the fact that I\Nhave a half-breed brother
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.94,0:51:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,whose heart I wanted\Nto run my trident through.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.87,0:51:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But now that you're finally\Nhere before me, I must admit...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.09,0:51:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I am conflicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.59,0:51:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You want conflict,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.89,0:51:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,why don't you take these\Nchains off, little brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.56,0:51:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll see who\Ngets run through.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.86,0:51:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I see you've brought\Nour mother's weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.87,0:51:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that why you've come\Nhere after all this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.57,0:51:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,To kill me?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.17,0:51:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I came here to stop a maniac\Nfrom destroying the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.98,0:51:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.91,0:51:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And how do you plan\Nto stop the atrocities
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.75,0:51:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that the surface\Ncontinues to commit?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.68,0:52:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Because for a century,\Nthey have polluted our waters
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.42,0:52:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and poisoned our children.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.79,0:52:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, their skies\Nburn and our oceans boil.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.46,0:52:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And you've come all this way to\Ntake sides against your own people?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.07,0:52:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no sides\Nin a war like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.24,0:52:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You have clearly chosen a side and\Ncome here to challenge the throne.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.97,0:52:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's what it takes\Nto stop your war.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.08,0:52:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you invoking the\NCombat of the Kings?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.95,0:52:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Call it whatever you want.\NI call it an ass-whooping.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.25,0:52:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, perhaps\Nthat's how we'll proceed.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.79,0:52:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- Your Majesty!\N- Orm, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.55,0:52:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.96,0:52:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If I defeat the\Nfirstborn son of Atlanna
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.99,0:52:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in a formal challenge\Nin front of everyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.46,0:52:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,then all Seven Kingdoms will have\Nto concede that I am the one true king.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.56,0:52:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Majesty, there is no\Nvictory in defeating the ignorant.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.57,0:52:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Your brother is\Nclearly an imbecile.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.84,0:52:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Highness, he\Ndoesn't know our ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.11,0:53:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he's about\Nto get an education.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.78,0:53:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you officially\Nchallenging me?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.75,0:53:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hell yes, I challenge\Nyou. And when I win...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.95,0:53:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you win,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.48,0:53:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I will cease all immediate\Naction. The war is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.06,0:53:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I win...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.39,0:53:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You're over.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.36,0:53:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.89,0:53:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.53,0:53:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Challenge has been\Nmade, and I accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.57,0:53:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare him for\Nthe Ring of Fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.04,0:53:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait. The ring of what?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.36,0:53:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How could you be so foolish\Nto let Orm bait you into a fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.23,0:53:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to me like I just\Nsolved all of our problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.93,0:53:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I beat him in a battle,\Nwar's over, I get to go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.23,0:53:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a formidable\Nfighter on land,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.47,0:54:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but here you're out of\Nyour element, literally.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.00,0:54:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Orm has spent his\Nentire life underwater,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.81,0:54:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,training to be a warrior,\Ntraining to be the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.51,0:54:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You taught me how\Nto fight, Cobra Kai.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.68,0:54:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if you\Nremember anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.55,0:54:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what's with the big fork?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.92,0:54:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a trident. Now,\Ndefend yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.25,0:54:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.76,0:54:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll teach you this move when\Nyou've mastered the trident.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.24,0:55:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.74,0:55:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This thing is so big and\Nawkward. Why can't I use a sword?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.81,0:55:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That's your mother's trident.\NA traditional weapon of royalty.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.58,0:55:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll never be a king\Nuntil you've mastered it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.18,0:55:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Why has she never\Ncome to see me, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.85,0:55:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you, when you're ready...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.98,0:55:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop lying to me! I've done\Neverything you ever asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.09,0:55:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And every time I pass a\Ntest, you make up another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.92,0:55:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,When am I gonna be good enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.26,0:55:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Does she not love me?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.13,0:55:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mother loved you more\Nthan anything in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.37,0:55:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But she had to return to\NAtlantis to keep you safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.21,0:55:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Her marriage to King Orvax\Nwas arranged a long time ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.58,0:55:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so she had to marry him...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.28,0:55:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And bear him a son, Prince Orm.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.75,0:55:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,When Orvax eventually\Nfound out about you,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.08,0:55:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,he became\Noverwhelmed with jealousy
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.65,0:56:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and sacrificed her to the\Ncreatures of the Trench.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.06,0:56:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying\Nthey executed her?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.86,0:56:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Because she had me?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.81,0:56:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.65,0:56:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.45,0:56:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I have something for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.36,0:56:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It belonged to my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.09,0:56:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.96,0:56:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think she would have enjoyed\Nwatching her sons murder each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.03,0:56:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand your fear\Nand your reluctance, Mera.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.57,0:56:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I truly do. I don't want war...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.91,0:56:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't patronize me!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.31,0:56:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.78,0:56:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're doing flies\Nin the face of everything
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.48,0:57:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that your mother taught\Nus when we were children.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.45,0:57:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If she were here...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.55,0:57:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But she's not here, is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.52,0:57:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,1What my mother\Ntaught us was treason.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.99,0:57:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't follow in her wake.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.79,0:57:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All right! So, this is the\Nbig, old ring of fire, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.73,0:57:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,How's it work? I just\Nkick your ass right here?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.47,0:57:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Vulko.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.87,0:57:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you escort my\Nbetrothed to the royal box?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.29,0:57:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go, Lady Mera.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.63,0:57:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Down here, we have a\Nlegend about the Karathen,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.66,0:57:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,an ancient sea monster so powerful\Nthat even King Atlan himself feared it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.57,0:57:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, he imprisoned it in\Nthe depths of the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.97,0:58:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that abyss, the creature\Nbides its time waiting to rise again.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.68,0:58:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Atlantis has been\Nlying in wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.31,0:58:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, the beast has awakened.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.82,0:58:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a time when I wanted\Nto meet you more than anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.26,0:58:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Get to know my little brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.46,0:58:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Let him know that he wasn't\Nalone, that we were in it together.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.61,0:58:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If only I had known what a\Ndick you would turn out to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.34,0:58:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You were the reason\Nour mother was executed.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.32,0:58:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've hated\Nyou for it ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.19,0:58:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But I do not want\Nto kill you, Arthur.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.89,0:58:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to give\Nyou one chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.79,0:58:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.16,0:58:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not ever come\Nback to Atlantis.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.60,0:59:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not going to win this.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.54,0:59:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,A war is coming to the surface\Nwhether you like it or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.34,0:59:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And I am bringing the wrath\Nof the seven seas with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.11,0:59:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You know I can't\Nlet that happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.55,0:59:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.99,0:59:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.56,0:59:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The Ring of Fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.20,0:59:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.94,0:59:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.61,0:59:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.12,0:59:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,People of Atlantis, hear me!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.75,0:59:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,My brother has come from the\Nsurface to challenge me for the throne.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.36,1:00:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us settle his claim\Nin the ancient way.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.59,1:00:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,By bloodshed do the\Ngods make known their will!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.57,1:00:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Traitor!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.74,1:00:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Traitor!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.35,1:00:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll never be king!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.13,1:00:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Never thought I'd see the\Nday when my own father
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.90,1:00:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,would bow before\Nthe king of Atlantis.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.74,1:00:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The surface-dwellers drew first\Nblood. What would you have us do?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.77,1:00:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Beg them for mercy?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.24,1:00:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I detest the surface\Nas much as you do.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.61,1:00:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But don't you find the timing\Nof all of this a bit convenient?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.32,1:01:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But you wouldn't be\Nthat gullible, would you?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.89,1:01:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You want this\Nwar too, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.83,1:01:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It is past time the surface-dwellers\Nlearned their place in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.43,1:01:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If this is how it must\Nbe done, then so be it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.00,1:01:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You have our mother's trident.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.41,1:01:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Powerful, but flawed like her.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.64,1:01:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I wield my father's.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.28,1:01:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And it has never known defeat!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.63,1:02:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I promised Atlanna\NI'd protect him.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.41,1:02:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't a competition.\NIt's an execution.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.79,1:04:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the one true king!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.14,1:05:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You waiting for an\Ninvitation? Get in!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.99,1:05:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Mera!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.32,1:05:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah. So, what's the plan?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.06,1:05:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The plan was to recover Atlan's\Ntrident, then challenge Orm.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.20,1:05:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so we're doing\Nthings a little out of order.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.93,1:05:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit happens.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.50,1:05:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Heads up! We got\Na bogey on our six!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.44,1:05:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,- What does that even mean?\N- Bad guys behind us.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.71,1:05:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- Then just say that!\N- Bad guys behind us!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.01,1:07:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, whoa, wait, you said\Nwe couldn't go over these walls.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.08,1:07:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- I did!\N- You said there were hydro-cannons!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.08,1:07:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I did, now shut up!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.69,1:07:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, shit!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.68,1:07:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.05,1:07:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.78,1:07:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not dead yet! But\NI'm hoping he'll think we are.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.52,1:07:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.00,1:07:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, hold this.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.33,1:07:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.73,1:07:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- Listen, it worked for Pinocchio.\N- Who?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.57,1:08:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind. Come\Nhere, get in. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.34,1:08:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Great. So we're getting eaten.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.00,1:08:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you even\Ndoing this, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.23,1:08:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.00,1:08:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hear them sometimes,\Nand they can hear me.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.57,1:08:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Because you're\Nboth big, dumb animals.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.44,1:08:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hey, I just saved your life.\N- I saved yours first!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.48,1:08:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,She said, "Coast is clear."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.48,1:08:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, where to now?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.85,1:08:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,To the ocean of sand\Nyour people call the Sahara.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.42,1:08:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.51,1:09:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't usually take charters,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.12,1:09:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,but I don't usually get\Npaid in pirate treasure.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.65,1:09:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for the ride, buddy.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.92,1:09:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, man.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.89,1:09:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.66,1:09:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never been\Nso high up before.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.60,1:09:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Or so far from home.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.60,1:09:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But at least you have a home.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.27,1:09:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Not anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.80,1:09:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I can never go back.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.50,1:09:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I betrayed everything when I\Nsaved you from the coliseum.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.38,1:09:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but you're engaged to the\Nking. They have to take you back.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.65,1:09:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Atlantis is many\Nwonderful things.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.82,1:09:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But forgiving, it is not.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.72,1:09:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but you're royalty.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.05,1:10:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So was your mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.36,1:10:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If I went back now, I'd be\Nsacrificed to the Trench.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.23,1:10:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Even my own father\Nwouldn't take me back.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.47,1:10:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Look on the bright side,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.40,1:10:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,now you don't have to marry some\Ntool bag that you're not in love with.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.67,1:10:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,My obligation isn't to love.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.87,1:10:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It is to my family\Nand my nation,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.44,1:10:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've turned my back on both.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.81,1:10:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes, you\Nhave to do what's right,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.58,1:10:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,even if your heart\Naches against it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.34,1:10:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Highness.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.74,1:10:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The tracker places Princess\NMera here, in the Deserter Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.48,1:10:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You said she was dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.51,1:10:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently not.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.42,1:11:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Then your brother\Nstill lives as well?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.19,1:11:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Not for long.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.52,1:11:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain Murk, assemble\Na strike force immediately.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.52,1:11:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No! Mera is to be arrested\Nand safely returned to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.26,1:11:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,She betrayed the throne.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.43,1:11:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,She is a daughter of Xebel.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.83,1:11:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If any harm befalls\Nher, our coalition is over.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.80,1:11:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Highness,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.37,1:11:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,we are now entering the waters\Nof the Fishermen Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.77,1:11:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Securing the alliance of\Nthe other two kingdoms
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.87,1:11:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,should be our immediate concern.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.11,1:11:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,My vizier is correct. As usual.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.09,1:11:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Arrest them and bring back\NKing Nereus' daughter unharmed.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.48,1:12:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We're here!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.38,1:12:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.65,1:12:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there anything nearby?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.19,1:12:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing but desert for\Nhundreds of K's, mate!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.29,1:12:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,- Nothing but desert.\N- He's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.33,1:12:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hey! What are you doing?\N- Wait! No! Oh...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.10,1:12:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,She just jumped! She\Ndidn't have a parachute!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.97,1:12:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Redheads! You gotta love 'em.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.62,1:12:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.90,1:12:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're crazier\Nthan I thought!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.70,1:13:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,A-ha!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.24,1:13:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This way.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.79,1:13:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You were defeated the last time\Nbecause your surface weapons failed you.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.33,1:13:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ours will not.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.87,1:13:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's prototype armor
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.40,1:13:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}for the next generation\NAtlantean soldier.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.27,1:13:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Revenge is something\Nwe Atlanteans understand.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.01,1:13:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You will lead my finest\Ncommandos as your personal army
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.38,1:13:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to hunt down the\Nhalf-breed abomination.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.95,1:13:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I cannot touch them, but you\Ncan. He's fled to your world.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.45,1:13:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Kill him and the woman he's\Nwith, and you will be rewarded.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.92,1:13:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Killing him is my reward.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.69,1:14:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- The crown jewel.\N- Still experimental.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.63,1:14:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Converts water into\Nbeams of energized plasma.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.67,1:15:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.27,1:15:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I'm gonna\Nneed a bigger helmet.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.78,1:15:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the tribes of Atlantis\Nbroke off and settled here
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.38,1:15:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,when this region\Nwas still an inland sea.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.55,1:15:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When the water dried up,\Nthey perished along with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.38,1:15:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Perished? Yeah, that's terrific.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.12,1:15:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We're getting close now.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.35,1:15:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah? Close to\Nwhat? Dying of thirst?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.82,1:15:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Close to getting\Npunched in the face!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.79,1:15:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, Fight Club, I know you're\Nnew to how things work up here.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.59,1:15:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you look\Naround? We are lost.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.90,1:15:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that over\Nthere? Hey, what is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.50,1:15:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Nada. This place is a wasteland.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.27,1:15:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the one who calls\Nthis wasteland a home.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.77,1:15:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't my home!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.40,1:15:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like the whole\Nsurface looks like this!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.24,1:15:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, of course not.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.17,1:15:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You've also got disgusting cities\Nwhose sewers empty out into our ocean
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.41,1:16:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and whole mountains\Nmade out of trash.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.31,1:16:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And, oh, you've\Ngot great factories
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.01,1:16:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that do nothing but belch\Nout filth and melt ice caps.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.92,1:16:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Point taken. Listen.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.98,1:16:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we got some\Nidiots running the show,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.45,1:16:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,but we've got some\Ngood things too, all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.46,1:16:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We got green forests and big\Nmountains and beautiful lakes.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.72,1:16:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd love 'em. They're\Nlike little baby oceans.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.56,1:16:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you trying to provoke me?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.40,1:16:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just saying you cannot judge\Na place before you've even seen it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.10,1:16:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You've judged\NAtlantis on far less.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.34,1:16:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Would you just\Nstop it with that? No.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.87,1:16:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Your stupid Atlantean GPS just\Ntold you to jump out of an airplane
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.48,1:16:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,over the middle of the desert,\Nand now we are stranded.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.75,1:16:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're the next true\Nking, we're doomed.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.71,1:17:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That was awesome.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.22,1:17:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Look what I found.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.06,1:17:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What you found?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.36,1:17:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.77,1:17:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Check this place out.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.07,1:17:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This is badass!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.28,1:17:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Hall of Armory.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.74,1:17:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Where the legends say\NAtlan's trident was forged.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.45,1:17:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think they're\Nlegends anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.82,1:17:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Vulko was right.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.79,1:17:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's real.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.57,1:18:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.33,1:18:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.30,1:18:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course it's not working.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.30,1:18:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been sitting here collecting dust\Nsince before the Sahara was a desert.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.88,1:18:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Man!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.64,1:18:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,"Since before the\NSahara was a desert."
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.68,1:18:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for\Nrepeating what I just said.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.85,1:18:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's completely dried out.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.65,1:18:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just say you\Ndo your best thinking
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.22,1:18:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're not thinking at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.22,1:19:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, now hold still.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.29,1:19:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.56,1:19:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We need water, and\Nyou're the closest source.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.70,1:19:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, hold still.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.47,1:19:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.50,1:19:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Show-off.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.50,1:19:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I could have just peed on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.58,1:19:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,King Atlan.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.75,1:20:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In this trident resides\Nthe power of Atlantis.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.89,1:20:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In the wrong hands, it\Nwould bring destruction.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.80,1:20:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But in the hands\Nof the true heir,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.06,1:20:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}it would unite all our\Nkingdoms above and below.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.17,1:20:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If you seek my power,\Nyou must prove your worth.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.11,1:20:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Journey beyond the edge of\Nthe world to the Hidden Sea.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.64,1:20:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Look inside the bottle\Nfor the charted path.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.91,1:20:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Only in the hands of the\Ntrue king can he truly see.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.89,1:20:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.03,1:20:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't let Orm find this.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.67,1:20:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.94,1:20:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.48,1:21:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't we have\Nwritten it down first?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.28,1:21:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I memorized it. Didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.98,1:21:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah. Totally.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.12,1:21:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What'd he just say?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.25,1:21:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,"Something something trident."
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.74,1:21:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,"Look inside the bottle\Nfor the charted path."
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.88,1:21:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's our next stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.47,1:23:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm starting to think you actually\Nlike these surface-dwellers.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.38,1:23:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be wrong to judge a\Nplace I've never seen before.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.45,1:23:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be right back.\NDon't go anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.07,1:23:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, apparently, it's just right\Nup on the hill. A big old castle.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.94,1:23:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just learned\Nsomething very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.38,1:23:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You risked our lives based on\Nsomething you read in a children's book?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.28,1:23:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, it's a book?\NHow about that?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.59,1:23:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.99,1:24:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it from the movie.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.89,1:24:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,King Nereus, I had hoped\Nour people had evolved
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.33,1:24:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond that ancient notion
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.50,1:24:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that war with the\Nsurface is inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.74,1:24:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the position\Nof the Fishermen
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.57,1:24:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that when the time comes to make\Nourselves known to the landsmen,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.84,1:24:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it should be to educate\Nthem, not to destroy them.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.01,1:24:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I admire your lofty\Naspirations, King Ricou.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.52,1:24:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But I suspect they are but clouds\Nof ink hiding the heart of a coward.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.52,1:24:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,How dare you!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.93,1:24:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Please. I implore you.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.23,1:24:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a kingdom of bloated\Nphilosophers and flaccid poets
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.03,1:24:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,whose waters have grown\Nstagnant, and it sickens me.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.18,1:25:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,My King!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.68,1:25:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The king is dead!\NLong live his heir.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.19,1:25:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Princess.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.42,1:25:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare your armies,\NYour Highness.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.03,1:25:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We move against the\NBrine Kingdom at once.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.04,1:25:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What did the\Nrecording say, again?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.11,1:25:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,"Journey beyond the edge of\Nthe world to the Hidden Sea.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.08,1:25:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,"Look in the bottle\Nfor the charted path.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.18,1:25:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,"Only in the hands of the\Ntrue king can he truly see."
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.18,1:25:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,"Look in the bottle\Nfor the charted path."
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.12,1:25:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.29,1:25:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, man.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.36,1:25:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.56,1:25:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow. That's awesome.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.93,1:25:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me see.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.47,1:25:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow. But how do you\Nknow where to point it?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.67,1:25:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, let me see.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.20,1:25:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the last line?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.91,1:26:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,"Only in the hands of the\Ntrue king can he truly see."
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.38,1:26:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,"Only in the\Nhands of the true..."
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.58,1:26:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Marcus Agrippa.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.71,1:26:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a great general,\Nbut he wasn't a king.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.55,1:26:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither was Scipio.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.35,1:26:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know all this stuff?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.02,1:26:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of my pops. He\Nmade sure I knew my history.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.12,1:26:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,None of these guys are\Nkings, except this guy. Romulus.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.43,1:26:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,First king of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.53,1:26:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,"Only in the hands of the\Ntrue king can he truly see."
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.68,1:26:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There it is. That's our heading.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.68,1:26:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Let me see.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.89,1:26:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We did it!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.06,1:26:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.02,1:26:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not bad for\Nan imbecile, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.26,1:26:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Not bad at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.48,1:27:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Mera.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.61,1:27:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,"Loathsomeness waits\Nand dreams in the deep,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.45,1:27:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,"and decay spreads over\Nthe tottering cities of men."
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.43,1:27:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Get back!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.10,1:27:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Arthur!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.17,1:27:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I order you to stand down!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.88,1:27:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Princess Mera, you've been\Ncharged with high treason.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.40,1:28:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Who the hell are you?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.73,1:28:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe this will jog your memory.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.81,1:28:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the guy from the sub.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.98,1:28:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.79,1:29:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But now I have Atlantean steel.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.86,1:29:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Call me "Black Manta."
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.91,1:29:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You thought you could walk away?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.99,1:29:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I told you\Nnot to make this a habit.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.51,1:29:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't run.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.61,1:30:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You owe me blood!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.88,1:30:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,How'd you find me?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.55,1:30:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Your lady friend has people\Nwho like to keep tabs on her.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.56,1:31:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.16,1:32:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.80,1:32:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody, inside. Get inside.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.74,1:32:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll show you the same\Nmercy you showed my father.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.85,1:32:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And gut you like\Nthe fish you are!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.86,1:34:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Arthur!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.04,1:34:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Mera, they're tracking you.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.54,1:34:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.67,1:34:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They're tracking you.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.22,1:34:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Arthur, stay with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.06,1:34:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Arthur, wake up! Arthur.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.88,1:35:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.68,1:35:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you steal a boat?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.31,1:35:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Are the boats at the\Nmarina not for public use?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.45,1:35:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No, those belong to people.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.62,1:35:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.19,1:35:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Those were Orm's\Nelite commandos.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.92,1:35:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But the one who led\Nthem, he wasn't Atlantean.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.23,1:35:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never seen him before.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.60,1:35:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I have.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.26,1:35:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He and his father were pirates.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.23,1:36:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And he blames me\Nfor his father's death.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.80,1:36:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They picked a dangerous\Nline of trade. It's not your fault.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.21,1:36:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not how it feels.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.18,1:36:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It was up to me,\Nand I let him die.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.15,1:36:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I could've saved\Nhim, but I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.05,1:36:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, I made an enemy,\Nand he could have hurt you.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.02,1:36:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And that would\Nhave been my fault.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.43,1:36:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he's behind us now.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.76,1:36:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's what lies ahead\Nthat should concern us.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.97,1:36:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The charted path leads to\Nthe Kingdom of the Trench.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.94,1:36:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Are those the same\Ncreatures that killed my mother?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.01,1:36:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:41.38,1:36:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,She was taken there\Nand sacrificed to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.48,1:36:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's become a place of death.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.65,1:36:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We know next to nothing\Nabout what's down there.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.99,1:36:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We should turn back.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:54.22,1:36:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We can still warn the surface. Try\Nand prepare them for what's coming.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.03,1:36:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn back?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.63,1:37:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, I learned from a young\Nage not to show weakness.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.67,1:37:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay? I solve my problems\Nwith my anger and my fists.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:05.90,1:37:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a blunt instrument,\Nand I'm damn good at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.91,1:37:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But I've done nothing but get\Nmy ass kicked this whole trip.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.38,1:37:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm no leader. I'm not a king.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.41,1:37:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I do not work or\Nplay well with others.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.15,1:37:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can't let you die trying to\Nturn me into something that I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.85,1:37:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You think you're unworthy to lead\Nbecause you're of two different worlds.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.56,1:37:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But that is exactly\Nwhy you are worthy.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.70,1:37:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You are the bridge\Nbetween land and sea.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.27,1:37:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The only question is...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.51,1:37:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.96,1:38:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The tracking on Lady Mera\Nis still dark, Your Highness.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.79,1:38:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Vulko.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:07.03,1:38:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,My trusted vizier
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.90,1:38:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,who has stood by the throne\Nsince my father sat upon it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.64,1:38:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you any advice\Nfor me as this war begins?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.54,1:38:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I have already\Ngiven it, My King.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.68,1:38:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But I will stand by your\Ndecision, as always.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:24.81,1:38:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,My decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.32,1:38:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,To protect it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.12,1:38:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,While you betray it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:34.66,1:38:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You think I do not\Nknow of your treachery?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:38.19,1:38:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That you have remained loyal\Nto my mother's bastard son.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.50,1:38:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That you have spent years training\Nhim to take the throne from me.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.94,1:38:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not deny it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.75,1:38:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I do not.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:58.48,1:38:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.25,1:39:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the pureblood.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.12,1:39:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I have devoted\Nmy life to Atlantis.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.16,1:39:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted nothing to do with\Nit. You swore to serve the throne!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:10.66,1:39:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I do serve it.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.66,1:39:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Arthur may only\Nbe half-Atlantean,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.33,1:39:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but he's already twice\Nthe king you'll ever be.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.77,1:39:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Take him.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.44,1:39:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But make sure he has a view.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:10.54,1:41:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell are these things?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.18,1:41:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The Trench! We're here!
Dialogue: 0,1:41:16.55,1:41:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,- There are too many of them!\N- Come on, inside!
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.96,1:41:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They're from the depths.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:30.03,1:41:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They're scared\Nof the light. Here!
Dialogue: 0,1:41:44.04,1:41:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.15,1:41:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You ready to jump?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:00.42,1:43:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Over there!
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.69,1:43:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That thing will tear us apart.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:38.69,1:43:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have a choice!
Dialogue: 0,1:44:00.45,1:44:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Arthur!
Dialogue: 0,1:44:05.42,1:44:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Mera!
Dialogue: 0,1:44:37.85,1:44:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Mera!
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.05,1:44:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Mera!
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.71,1:45:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Mera!
Dialogue: 0,1:45:06.91,1:45:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Mera!
Dialogue: 0,1:45:52.16,1:45:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Arthur.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:54.23,1:45:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:33.80,1:46:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,King Orvax sacrificed me\Nto the Trench, but I survived.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:38.54,1:46:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I fought my way through as\Nyou did, and I ended up here.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:42.01,1:46:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been here\Nalone for 20 years?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:43.84,1:46:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:45.31,1:46:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Come. Sit here.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:51.72,1:46:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You must forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:54.32,1:46:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive me for everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:56.96,1:46:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This happened\Nbecause you had me.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:59.46,1:47:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Not for having you.\NNone of this is your fault.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:04.33,1:47:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I made a choice.\NI had to leave...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:07.23,1:47:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,To save you, to\Nsave your father.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:13.74,1:47:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me. Tell me about him.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:16.74,1:47:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:21.91,1:47:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He still walks to\Nthe end of that dock.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:26.22,1:47:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Every morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:30.29,1:47:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:34.86,1:47:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:43.97,1:47:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you ever come back?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:51.04,1:47:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the portal that brought\Nyou here won't let us return.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:55.28,1:47:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The trident is the\Nonly way back.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:58.92,1:48:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is guarded\Nby the Karathen.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:05.16,1:48:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The creature from\Nour legends, it's real.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:07.73,1:48:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It lies beyond the waterfall.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:14.93,1:48:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go with you. We\Ncan fight it together.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:17.27,1:48:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:18.64,1:48:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too powerful.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:20.47,1:48:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I've tried many\Ntimes over the years.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:24.31,1:48:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The creature will only\Nallow the true king to pass.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:30.81,1:48:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You're afraid.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:35.22,1:48:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:37.79,1:48:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:40.62,1:48:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You're ready.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:43.29,1:48:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Atlantis has always had a king.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:46.93,1:48:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it needs something more.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:49.13,1:48:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But what could be\Ngreater than a king?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:51.77,1:48:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,A hero.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:54.81,1:48:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,A king fights\Nonly for his nation.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:58.98,1:49:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You fight for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:29.80,1:50:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You do not belong here.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:35.57,1:50:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I have guarded the trident against\Nfalse kings since the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:42.15,1:50:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And for a thousand years
Dialogue: 0,1:50:44.55,1:50:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I have seen the greatest\Nchampions try and fail.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:50.35,1:50:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But never have I sensed\None as unworthy as you.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:56.89,1:51:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You dare come here with\Nyour tainted mongrel blood
Dialogue: 0,1:51:04.13,1:51:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to claim Atlantis'\Ngreatest treasure?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:09.97,1:51:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So be it...
Dialogue: 0,1:51:12.61,1:51:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Half-breed.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:33.86,1:51:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You thought yourself worthy?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:37.07,1:51:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You thought yourself a king?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:40.20,1:51:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You dishonor this\Nplace with your presence.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:44.61,1:51:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:53.28,1:51:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right. I am a\Nhalf-breed mongrel.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:57.95,1:52:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But I did not come here\Nbecause I thought I was worthy.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:00.89,1:52:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I know I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:02.79,1:52:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand me?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:06.86,1:52:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:08.63,1:52:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No mortal has conversed\Nwith me since King Atlan.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:16.54,1:52:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:20.54,1:52:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm nobody.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:24.21,1:52:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I came because I had no choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:28.55,1:52:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I came to save my home\Nand the people that I love.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:35.26,1:52:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I came because the\Ntrident is their only hope.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.36,1:52:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And if that's not good enough...
Dialogue: 0,1:52:44.00,1:52:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Then screw you.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:47.50,1:52:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No man has ever freed\Nthe trident from Atlan's grip.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:55.38,1:52:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Should he deem you unworthy...
Dialogue: 0,1:52:58.58,1:53:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I haven't feasted in eons,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:03.95,1:53:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and I am famished.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:37.05,1:54:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The one true king.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:52.56,1:54:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, the Brine are\Npowerful, savage brutes,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:55.70,1:55:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,but a swift assault aimed directly\Nat their leadership will turn the tide.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:00.24,1:55:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Defeat the Brine King,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:02.07,1:55:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and you will command the\Ngreatest military might on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:07.61,1:55:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, we unite our kingdoms.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:11.28,1:55:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow, we scorch the surface!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:14.18,1:55:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Rise, Atlantis!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:35.24,1:55:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Death to the Atlantean hagfish!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:43.88,1:55:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We will not bow to Atlantis.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:46.18,1:55:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We're gonna give them a\Nfight that they will never forget!
Dialogue: 0,1:56:57.15,1:56:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,No! We need him!
Dialogue: 0,1:57:02.16,1:57:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Join me or die.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:03.76,1:57:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You expect me to address\Nyou as Your Highness?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:07.33,1:57:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Not Your Highness.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:10.76,1:57:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Call me...
Dialogue: 0,1:57:13.03,1:57:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Ocean Master.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:14.74,1:57:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You can take my army,\Nyou soft-bellied slug.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:18.64,1:57:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But you will never\Nhave my allegiance!
Dialogue: 0,1:57:22.21,1:57:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So be it!
Dialogue: 0,1:57:55.34,1:57:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What the...
Dialogue: 0,1:58:31.98,1:58:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The king has risen.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:41.32,1:58:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Attack!
Dialogue: 0,2:00:42.24,2:00:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There are too many casualties.\NWe have to stop the fighting now.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:44.94,2:00:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll find my father. But\Nyou must defeat Orm.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:49.61,2:00:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And what if I can't?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:51.18,2:00:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Last time, he was\Nin his element.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:54.42,2:00:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, make\Nhim fight in yours.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:24.55,2:01:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,2:01:26.49,2:01:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- What was the plan, again?\N- The plan is to not get killed.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:30.86,2:01:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, good plan.\NDon't get killed.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:06.52,2:02:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The Trench! He\Ncommands the Trench!
Dialogue: 0,2:02:08.56,2:02:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,2:02:26.91,2:02:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Stand down! Let her pass.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:28.65,2:02:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, Father,\Nhe has the trident.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:31.85,2:02:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you think\Nthis war is necessary,
Dialogue: 0,2:02:34.22,2:02:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but Arthur is king by\Nour most sacred law.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:36.79,2:02:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you turn your\Nback on that now,
Dialogue: 0,2:02:38.46,2:02:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,then the Atlantis you're\Nfighting for is already dead.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:40.76,2:02:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true! The half-breed\Nwields King Atlan's trident.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:43.83,2:02:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He commands the sea!
Dialogue: 0,2:02:47.16,2:02:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Then that half-breed\Nis your king.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:06.38,2:04:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Vulko! Come on,\Nhe needs our help!
Dialogue: 0,2:04:08.88,2:04:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't! Look.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:10.78,2:04:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The people must bear witness.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:18.56,2:04:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That trident doesn't\Nchange what you are.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:21.92,2:04:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,A half-breed bastard.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:26.06,2:04:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Atlantis will never\Naccept you as its king.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:32.10,2:04:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then by bloodshed...
Dialogue: 0,2:04:35.71,2:04:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Do the gods make\Nknown their will.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:07.17,2:05:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yield the throne. Yield it!
Dialogue: 0,2:06:45.30,2:06:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Finish it.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:46.50,2:06:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yield the throne.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:47.87,2:06:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Mercy is not our way.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:51.24,2:06:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you haven't\Nnoticed, brother...
Dialogue: 0,2:06:58.85,2:07:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm not one of you.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:00.72,2:07:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Do it!
Dialogue: 0,2:07:04.19,2:07:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,- Kill me!\N- No!
Dialogue: 0,2:07:08.83,2:07:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That is enough killing.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:18.00,2:07:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:19.90,2:07:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my son.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:30.71,2:07:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a long story.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:32.85,2:07:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell ya later.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:35.35,2:07:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,2:07:43.16,2:07:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't understand.\NWe thought...
Dialogue: 0,2:07:46.33,2:07:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:47.90,2:07:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Arthur saved me.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:53.40,2:07:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- You're with him?\N- I am.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:58.24,2:08:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You're both my children,\Nand I love you so much.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:03.34,2:08:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But you have been misguided.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:06.95,2:08:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father taught you\Nthat there were two worlds.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:11.02,2:08:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:12.89,2:08:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The land and the sea
Dialogue: 0,2:08:16.93,2:08:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,are one.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:38.45,2:08:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,My queen.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:42.68,2:08:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Vulko.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:46.35,2:08:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Take him.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:48.16,2:08:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But make sure he has a view.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:57.50,2:08:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're ready,
Dialogue: 0,2:09:00.90,2:09:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,let's talk.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:16.95,2:09:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,People of Atlantis,\Ntoday began in bloodshed,
Dialogue: 0,2:09:21.09,2:09:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but let it end in joy.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:24.06,2:09:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I give you King\NArthur of Atlantis.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:28.60,2:09:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Hail to the king!
Dialogue: 0,2:09:30.30,2:09:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hail to the king!\N- Hail to the king!
Dialogue: 0,2:09:41.38,2:09:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what do I do now?
Dialogue: 0,2:09:44.31,2:09:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Be their king.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:47.32,2:09:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:48.68,2:09:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This is gonna be fun.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:42.80,2:10:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You came back. You're back.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:45.71,2:10:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:53.68,2:10:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My father was a\Nlighthouse keeper.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:57.39,2:10:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My mother was a queen.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:00.96,2:11:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They were never meant to meet...
Dialogue: 0,2:11:06.23,2:11:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But their love saved the world.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:10.83,2:11:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They made me what I am.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:13.43,2:11:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A son of the land,\Nand a king of the seas.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:18.71,2:11:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I am the protector of the deep.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:22.54,2:11:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I am...
Dialogue: 0,2:11:25.28,2:11:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Aquaman.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:36.24,2:14:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,2:14:41.44,2:14:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I spent 15 years
Dialogue: 0,2:14:42.98,2:14:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}at the United States\NInstitute of Marine Science...
Dialogue: 0,2:14:45.34,2:14:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- Weren't you fired?\N- ...studying oceanic phenomenon,
Dialogue: 0,2:14:48.51,2:14:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and this is the most conclusive\Nevidence we have to date.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:50.88,2:14:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Deep-sea seismographs have\Nrecorded explosions on the ocean floor.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:54.45,2:14:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We have satellite imagery
Dialogue: 0,2:14:56.66,2:14:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}of debris from Atlantean\Nwarships floating on the surface...
Dialogue: 0,2:14:59.02,2:15:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- Dr. Shin!\N- Will you please let me finish?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:00.83,2:15:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Here we go again. Atlantean?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:03.06,2:15:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes. The government\Ndoes not want us to know
Dialogue: 0,2:15:05.83,2:15:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}about the threat that\Nexists right here...
Dialogue: 0,2:15:07.40,2:15:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I wouldn't\Ndo that if I were you.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:21.98,2:15:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Atlantean\Ntechnology, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:23.92,2:15:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you tell me\Nhow you got this?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:26.05,2:15:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. But first,
Dialogue: 0,2:15:29.42,2:15:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you gotta tell me\Nhow to find him.
